    {
        "content": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I followed this tutorial to create a simple hello world sample module by following this tutorial:<br>\n<a href=\"https://wusyong.github.io/posts/rust-kernel-module-01/\">https://wusyong.github.io/posts/rust-kernel-module-01/</a></p>\n<p>After I build the kernel with the module hello world, it gives the following errors:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/WxZVemDMbrhF-KoXDBMcUpS8/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<p>How can I solve this problem?</p>",
        "id": 358483098,
        "sender_full_name": "LittleKaori",
        "timestamp": 1684162246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for the first error, remove the \"b\" string prefix before the strings in the <code>module</code> macro</p>",
        "id": 358490221,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1684163759
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what branch are you using?</p>",
        "id": 358490477,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1684163801
